1
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:32,030
[Echoes of a Thousand Moons]

2
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:35,050
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:36,560
Everyone,

4
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:36,580
[Fight to the Death; Never Be a Slave]

5
00:01:36,990 --> 00:01:37,920
attention!

6
00:01:53,470 --> 00:01:57,680
[Fight to the Death; Never Be a Slave]

7
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:03,090
Brigade Commander,

8
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:05,090
the regiment's direct units have assembled

9
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:06,750
and await your instructions!

10
00:02:18,329 --> 00:02:18,950
[87th Brigade,
National Revolutionary Army]

11
00:02:18,970 --> 00:02:19,770
[Liu Maoyuan, 806th Regiment Commander]

12
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:44,450
[Reclaim Our Lost Territory;
Restore Our Homeland]

13
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,000
I am Zhang Yunkui.

14
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,510
Here, I make a pact with you all.

15
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:52,040
With the enemy at our gates,

16
00:02:52,090 --> 00:02:53,410
whatever happened in the past,

17
00:02:53,410 --> 00:02:55,010
I'll leave it behind us.

18
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:56,740
However, from today onward,

19
00:02:56,740 --> 00:02:58,920
I'll go to the battlefield with you all

20
00:02:58,940 --> 00:03:00,180
to repay our country,

21
00:03:00,210 --> 00:03:01,420
to live and die together,

22
00:03:01,420 --> 00:03:02,590
and never retreat!

23
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,820
Do you agree?

24
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,800
Yes.

25
00:03:07,980 --> 00:03:08,850
Do you agree?

26
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:09,840
Yes!

27
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:11,890
Regimental Commander Liu.

28
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:12,490
Yes, sir!

29
00:03:12,980 --> 00:03:14,630
How should a deserter be dealt with?

30
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:16,210
To maintain discipline during wartime,

31
00:03:16,210 --> 00:03:17,070
any deserter caught

32
00:03:17,070 --> 00:03:18,600
may be executed on the spot!

33
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:32,950
Do you have anything to say?

34
00:03:36,690 --> 00:03:38,550
Officer in charge, step forward!

35
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:39,920
Yes, sir!

36
00:03:39,990 --> 00:03:40,930
Execute him.

37
00:03:41,210 --> 00:03:41,820
Yes, sir!

38
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:45,300
I've been wronged!

39
00:03:45,329 --> 00:03:46,540
I'm not a soldier!

40
00:03:46,570 --> 00:03:48,370
I was dragged here!

41
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,079
I'm not a soldier!

42
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:50,860
-Wait!
-Shut up!

43
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:52,660
-I was taken by force!
-Stop him!

44
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,170
What's going on? Make it clear.

45
00:04:04,380 --> 00:04:08,220
I'm just a cook at Zhengxing Restaurant!

46
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,440
I was walking down the street

47
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:14,750
when they grabbed me and took me here!

48
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:16,510
Who grabbed you?

49
00:04:16,910 --> 00:04:18,130
I dare not say.

50
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:19,880
Adjutant Zhao.

51
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:20,560
Yes, sir.

52
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,150
Don't move!

53
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:26,860
Don't move!

54
00:04:34,659 --> 00:04:35,350
Tell me,

55
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:36,670
who grabbed you?

56
00:04:40,570 --> 00:04:41,420
Speak.

57
00:04:45,450 --> 00:04:46,470
It was him!

58
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:47,980
It was him!

59
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,960
He forced me to lie

60
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,930
and claim I'd volunteered!

61
00:04:52,090 --> 00:04:53,159
If I spilled the beans,

62
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,680
he said he'd kill me!

63
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,640
It was him!

64
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:56,780
Anyone else?

65
00:04:57,890 --> 00:04:58,650
And...

66
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,010
And...

67
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,340
And...

68
00:05:01,690 --> 00:05:02,540
And...

69
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,280
And... And...

70
00:05:08,190 --> 00:05:09,190
Come here!

71
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:10,980
Him!

72
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:13,610
He hit me with his rifle butt!

73
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:14,530
And...

74
00:05:14,990 --> 00:05:16,140
And... And...

75
00:05:16,170 --> 00:05:17,120
And...

76
00:05:21,470 --> 00:05:22,280
Him!

77
00:05:22,660 --> 00:05:23,740
He kicked me!

78
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,200
He kicked me!

79
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:26,250
Let go of me!

80
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:27,060
And...

81
00:05:27,470 --> 00:05:28,140
And...

82
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:29,660
And...

83
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:32,480
And him!

84
00:05:32,510 --> 00:05:33,860
Come out!

85
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,820
He was just like him!

86
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,110
Said he'd kill me!

87
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,380
Officer!

88
00:05:39,490 --> 00:05:41,070
My righteous lord!

89
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,630
Please help me!

90
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,780
Help me!

91
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:46,850
Regimental Commander Liu.

92
00:05:46,850 --> 00:05:47,580
Yes, sir.

93
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,470
How many men like him

94
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,500
have you forcibly drafted in total?

95
00:05:56,490 --> 00:05:58,080
You were padding your payroll
with ghost soldiers,

96
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:58,920
and to avoid being found out,

97
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:01,120
you press-ganged men to fill the ranks?

98
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:02,430
What time is it now?

99
00:06:02,450 --> 00:06:04,980
Tell me the truth,
Regimental Commander Liu!

100
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,750
Brigade Commander,

101
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:13,660
we haven't been able to
replenish our recruits.

102
00:06:13,660 --> 00:06:15,280
It was a last resort.

103
00:06:15,390 --> 00:06:17,080
Across the whole regiment,

104
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:18,770
there are probably about 200 or so.

105
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:21,570
Their names have already been
recorded and filed.

106
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:23,240
You really have the nerve!

107
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,120
Sorry, sir.

108
00:06:25,530 --> 00:06:27,330
We were already understrength,

109
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:29,580
and now the enemy is at our gates.

110
00:06:29,690 --> 00:06:31,140
If we let them go now,

111
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,770
we really won't be able to
fight this battle.

112
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:34,920
Actually,

113
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:36,080
the higher-ups...

114
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:37,770
have been turning a blind eye

115
00:06:37,770 --> 00:06:38,920
to this too.

116
00:06:45,810 --> 00:06:46,920
Persuade them as best you can.

117
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,120
Keep those who are willing to stay.

118
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,159
For those who really don't want to,

119
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:50,960
don't assign them to combat units.

120
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,490
Put together a list and hand it to me.

121
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:53,760
I'll report it up the chain

122
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:55,159
and try to let them all go.

123
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,000
Yes.

124
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,560
My righteous lord!

125
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,900
I beg you, please let me go!

126
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:01,770
I...

127
00:07:02,310 --> 00:07:04,110
My lord, look!

128
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:06,380
I was supposed to get married!

129
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:08,620
I had just had a brand-new long gown made!

130
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:10,690
I was going to wear it to get married,

131
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,920
and they grabbed me and dragged me here!

132
00:07:13,050 --> 00:07:15,350
My lord, please let me go! Please!

133
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:16,310
Please let me go!

134
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,010
Please let me go...

135
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,130
I already gave my word

136
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,090
that all past offenses are forgiven.

137
00:07:23,090 --> 00:07:24,270
I can overlook

138
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,100
the fact that you forced conscription.

139
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,300
But there is one thing

140
00:07:27,610 --> 00:07:29,140
I must pursue.

141
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,000
Killing him—

142
00:07:31,020 --> 00:07:33,230
that was because he was a deserter.
He had it coming!

143
00:07:33,230 --> 00:07:34,200
But Company Commander Yu...

144
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:34,890
Yes, sir!

145
00:07:34,990 --> 00:07:36,230
Just now I said, wait.

146
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,130
Why did you still insist on firing?

147
00:07:38,130 --> 00:07:39,530
What did you mean by that?

148
00:07:45,890 --> 00:07:46,950
What are you doing?

149
00:07:47,010 --> 00:07:48,070
What are you doing?

150
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:49,840
Restrain him!

151
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:50,540
Move!

152
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:51,390
Let go!

153
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:52,450
Company Commander Yu,

154
00:07:52,450 --> 00:07:53,930
you not only violated
military regulations,

155
00:07:53,930 --> 00:07:55,670
but also attempted to
kill him to cover your tracks.

156
00:07:55,670 --> 00:07:56,900
You treat the lives of others as worthless

157
00:07:56,900 --> 00:07:58,600
and disgrace the honor of a soldier.

158
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,740
According to military law,

159
00:07:59,740 --> 00:08:01,270
how should you be punished?

160
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:03,420
His life means so little

161
00:08:03,510 --> 00:08:06,040
that it's not worth
answering for with yours?

162
00:08:08,130 --> 00:08:09,030
What do you mean?

163
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:10,560
You're going to execute me?

164
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:12,860
Yu Yuansheng, shut up!

165
00:08:15,260 --> 00:08:16,390
Brigade Commander.

166
00:08:21,640 --> 00:08:24,440
Brigadier, you're using me
to make an example, eh?

167
00:08:30,550 --> 00:08:31,610
Fine!

168
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:32,770
I admit

169
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,590
that I, Yu, was out of line!

170
00:08:35,870 --> 00:08:37,130
If the new commander

171
00:08:37,610 --> 00:08:39,470
can lead the men here to victory,

172
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:40,600
then I'll

173
00:08:41,260 --> 00:08:44,430
gladly serve as a blood sacrifice
for the 87th Brigade's banner!

174
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:45,560
Nothing more to say!

175
00:08:50,220 --> 00:08:50,900
Move!

176
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:52,050
Move!

177
00:08:52,180 --> 00:08:53,670
Pass a message to my mom!

178
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,450
Tell her...

179
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,170
Kneel!

180
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:57,800
Tell her I died in battle!

181
00:09:03,150 --> 00:09:03,940
Wait!

182
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:07,710
Brigade Commander,

183
00:09:07,710 --> 00:09:10,060
this guy Yu is a good fighter.

184
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,330
With the enemy right in front of us,

185
00:09:11,330 --> 00:09:12,530
it would be such a waste

186
00:09:12,530 --> 00:09:13,530
to kill him now.

187
00:09:15,310 --> 00:09:16,440
Brigade Commander.

188
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:23,800
Yu Yuansheng,

189
00:09:24,070 --> 00:09:25,870
do you have anything else to say?

190
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:27,530
Brigade Commander...

191
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:30,980
I want to die on the battlefield!

192
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:36,150
Soldiers,

193
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:38,960
the Japanese have already reached

194
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,070
our doorstep.

195
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:42,590
I don't care how you ended up here today.

196
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,200
I, Yunkui, sincerely ask you

197
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:46,100
to fight the enemy with me!

198
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,400
According to military regulations,

199
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,390
Yu Yuansheng should be executed
on the spot.

200
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:50,990
But a great battle is upon us.

201
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:53,060
Do you think he should die?

202
00:09:53,090 --> 00:09:54,200
Yes!

203
00:09:54,980 --> 00:09:55,860
Does he?

204
00:09:55,890 --> 00:09:56,920
He does!

205
00:09:57,550 --> 00:09:58,620
Where should he die?

206
00:09:58,620 --> 00:09:59,830
On the battlefield!

207
00:09:59,860 --> 00:10:00,650
Where?

208
00:10:00,780 --> 00:10:01,960
The battlefield!

209
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:06,140
Yu Yuansheng!

210
00:10:06,170 --> 00:10:06,900
Yes, sir!

211
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,290
Listen up,

212
00:10:08,530 --> 00:10:10,540
today I am not the one sparing your life.

213
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:12,400
It's because they pleaded for you

214
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,400
that I spared you!

215
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:14,850
Remember that!

216
00:10:14,870 --> 00:10:15,950
I will!

217
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,380
Return to your unit!

218
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,800
The shells are widely scattered.

219
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,400
From large-caliber naval guns.

220
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,730
That means the Japanese

221
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:33,930
are about to land.

222
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:36,770
The situation at Luodian
must already be critical!

223
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:37,590
Soon,

224
00:10:37,610 --> 00:10:39,540
you will receive orders to move out.

225
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:40,230
Everyone,

226
00:10:40,260 --> 00:10:42,660
-prepare for battle!
-Brigade Commander!

227
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,730
Brigade Commander,

228
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:46,750
urgent telegram
from Division Headquarters:

229
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,950
Japanese forces have landed at Wusong!

230
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:50,360
Our brigade is ordered to
move out immediately

231
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,090
and rush to reinforce Luodian!

232
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:54,800
Artillery Company Commander!

233
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:55,560
Yes, sir!

234
00:10:56,620 --> 00:10:57,490
How much ammunition do we have?

235
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:58,590
Since we just arrived here,

236
00:10:58,590 --> 00:11:00,190
our rear supplies aren't fully in yet!

237
00:11:00,190 --> 00:11:01,180
Currently,

238
00:11:01,220 --> 00:11:02,860
I only have two standard loads!

239
00:11:02,860 --> 00:11:03,960
Take all the ammunition

240
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,070
and follow the vanguard battalion!

241
00:11:05,070 --> 00:11:05,740
Yes, sir!

242
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,240
Regimental Commander Liu,
Regimental Commander Feng.

243
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:07,840
Sir!

244
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:08,500
Sir!

245
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:09,850
Notify all troops

246
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:11,210
to check weapons, equipment,

247
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:12,030
and supplies.

248
00:11:12,050 --> 00:11:13,140
In half an hour,

249
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:14,080
assemble and depart!

250
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,280
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

251
00:11:17,950 --> 00:11:19,280
My righteous lord!

252
00:11:19,450 --> 00:11:20,850
My righteous lord!

253
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:22,460
My lord!

254
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,130
My righteous lord!

255
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,520
My righteous lord!

256
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,200
My righteous lord!

257
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:29,920
Eyes front!

258
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:31,240
Run?

259
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,200
Double time!

260
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,650
Run again, and I'll kill you!

261
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:35,150
Is there no justice anymore?

262
00:11:35,150 --> 00:11:36,850
The lord said I could go!

263
00:11:36,990 --> 00:11:37,950
My lord!

264
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:39,720
Someone is settling a personal score
against me!

265
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,120
What are you wailing about?

266
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,780
You think you can out-wail me?

267
00:11:42,970 --> 00:11:44,180
You're now assigned to the logistics unit.

268
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:45,590
Return to your unit
and move out immediately!

269
00:11:45,590 --> 00:11:47,190
Stop wasting words with him.

270
00:11:49,690 --> 00:11:51,080
Sir, he knows he was wrong.

271
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:51,790
Move out! Let's move out!

272
00:11:51,790 --> 00:11:52,600
Keep up!

273
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:53,680
Keep up, everyone!

274
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:54,910
Hurry up!

275
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:56,820
Hurry up!

276
00:11:57,540 --> 00:12:03,340
[Shanghai Field Hospital]

277
00:11:58,090 --> 00:11:59,470
This is the place, right?

278
00:11:59,470 --> 00:12:00,920
Quick, this is the place!

279
00:12:01,860 --> 00:12:02,790
Keep up, keep up!

280
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:04,160
Careful!

281
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:04,610
Careful.

282
00:12:04,610 --> 00:12:05,290
Make way!

283
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:07,530
Quick, quick!

284
00:12:07,530 --> 00:12:08,530
Careful!

285
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:09,430
You can't go in!

286
00:12:09,430 --> 00:12:10,990
This is a field hospital—
no unauthorized entry.

287
00:12:10,990 --> 00:12:11,780
Go back.

288
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,800
We have a letter of recommendation.

289
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:16,070
Are you guys together?

290
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:16,630
-Yes.
-Right!

291
00:12:16,630 --> 00:12:17,440
We are together.

292
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,240
Wait a moment.

293
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,050
Dr. Sun!

294
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,870
Dr... Dr. Sun!

295
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:23,390
[Chengren High School]

296
00:12:22,020 --> 00:12:25,020
Some people are here
with a letter of recommendation.

297
00:12:27,230 --> 00:12:28,110
Sun Zheng.

298
00:12:28,410 --> 00:12:29,150
Luo Zuliang.

299
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:29,910
Wang Jianguang.

300
00:12:29,910 --> 00:12:30,770
It's all written there!

301
00:12:30,770 --> 00:12:31,510
It's written on there.

302
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:32,440
Wang Jianguang.

303
00:12:33,020 --> 00:12:34,390
Alright, come with me.

304
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,040
Let us in too!

305
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,320
Go back! Go back!

306
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,630
Let us in, officer!

307
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:42,720
What year are you in?

308
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,440
I'm a third-year student.

309
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,910
They're second-year students.

310
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:45,580
What can you do?

311
00:12:45,580 --> 00:12:46,780
We've performed basic surgical procedures,

312
00:12:46,780 --> 00:12:49,040
but our clinical experience is limited.

313
00:12:49,210 --> 00:12:50,700
Help care for the wounded for now,

314
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:52,250
then take turns observing surgeries.

315
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:52,990
Okay.

316
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,060
Dr. Sun,

317
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:56,350
a wounded soldier over there
is not doing well!

318
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:57,210
Go through this courtyard

319
00:12:57,210 --> 00:12:58,780
to the operating room in the back
and find Director Wang!

320
00:12:58,780 --> 00:12:59,660
Okay.

321
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:02,440
Make way! Make way!

322
00:13:02,440 --> 00:13:03,360
Make way!

323
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,910
We medical students
can be of real use here.

324
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:05,630
A shoe fell off!

325
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:07,050
Sun, you're a history major.

326
00:13:07,050 --> 00:13:08,630
Aren't you just here to cause trouble?

327
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:09,480
I can be like them,

328
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:10,740
helping carry things!

329
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,800
[Baijiazhai]

330
00:13:51,390 --> 00:13:53,830
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

331
00:13:55,090 --> 00:13:57,610
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

332
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:01,760
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

333
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,730
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

334
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:10,610
♪ Wrath sets on end my hair,
I lean on railings ♪

335
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:14,450
♪ Where I see
the drizzling rain has ceased ♪

336
00:14:16,430 --> 00:14:18,150
♪ Raising my eyes ♪

337
00:14:19,290 --> 00:14:21,220
♪ Towards the skies ♪

338
00:14:24,090 --> 00:14:26,000
♪ I heave long sighs ♪

339
00:14:27,830 --> 00:14:34,330
♪ I heave long sighs ♪

340
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:42,220
♪ I heave long sighs ♪

341
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:03,380
Guys...

342
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:08,270
♪ To dust is gone the fame
achieved in thirty years ♪

343
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:11,880
♪ Like cloud-veiled moon
the thousand-mile Plain disappears ♪

344
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,330
♪ Should youthful heads ♪

345
00:15:15,170 --> 00:15:19,250
♪ In vain turn grey ♪

346
00:15:20,610 --> 00:15:23,520
♪ We would regret for aye ♪

347
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:27,230
♪ We would regret for aye ♪

348
00:15:28,180 --> 00:15:31,010
♪ We would regret for aye ♪

349
00:15:32,010 --> 00:15:35,220
♪ We would regret for aye ♪

350
00:15:56,150 --> 00:16:01,170
[Temporary Brigade Headquarters—
Emperor Guan Temple, Baijiazhai Town]

351
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:18,120
Yunkui, well done!

352
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:20,060
Your first battle as commander,

353
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:22,180
and you've already taken Baijiazhai.

354
00:16:22,180 --> 00:16:25,360
This has taken a lot of pressure off
the neighboring units.

355
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,840
You've made a great start
as the new brigade commander.

356
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,880
I'll submit a commendation request

357
00:16:28,140 --> 00:16:31,610
[Division Headquarters Command Post]

358
00:16:30,420 --> 00:16:32,240
on your behalf to Army Headquarters!

359
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:34,120
But you must hold your ground there.

360
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:36,510
Baijiazhai is the junction

361
00:16:36,510 --> 00:16:37,670
with the right-wing forces.

362
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:41,240
The Japanese Army will definitely
choose to break through there.

363
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:42,750
You must not yield

364
00:16:41,290 --> 00:16:44,810
[Sun Huaiyi, Commander
of the 187th Division, NRA]

365
00:16:42,820 --> 00:16:44,030
an inch of ground!

366
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:45,120
Division Commander,

367
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,240
our troops have suffered severe casualties

368
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,360
and lack heavy firepower support.

369
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:49,600
Please assign
the division's artillery to me.

370
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:53,200
Yunkui, the division's artillery
has exhausted its ammunition

371
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,400
and is out of supplies.

372
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:55,550
Now you can

373
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,700
only rely on yourselves.

374
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:58,890
Division Commander,

375
00:16:58,890 --> 00:17:01,060
if not artillery,
at least give me one battalion.

376
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,170
Send me some more men,

377
00:17:02,170 --> 00:17:03,080
especially veterans.

378
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:04,540
Or some artillery shells.

379
00:17:05,540 --> 00:17:06,420
Yunkui,

380
00:17:06,569 --> 00:17:08,920
the entire front line
is under heavy pressure.

381
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:11,020
I've already personally submitted
a request to the Army Commander,

382
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:13,270
asking for reinforcements
from other theaters

383
00:17:13,270 --> 00:17:15,430
as soon as possible.

384
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:16,349
You...

385
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:18,849
must hold your ground.

386
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:22,510
Go to the front line.

387
00:17:37,310 --> 00:17:38,160
Hurry. Hurry!

388
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,330
This way.

389
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:42,070
Come on, this way.

390
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:43,530
Excuse me.

391
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,330
Coming through.

392
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,180
Make way. Coming through.

393
00:17:50,470 --> 00:17:52,190
[Casualty Tag]

394
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:53,960
Walking wounded, here!

395
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,290
Seriously wounded, follow me to the back!

396
00:17:56,620 --> 00:17:57,660
Here, this way!

397
00:17:59,830 --> 00:18:00,980
There's a spot here!

398
00:18:01,870 --> 00:18:02,740
Careful!

399
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:11,990
[Casualty Tag]

400
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:18,570
[Casualty Tag]

401
00:18:56,190 --> 00:18:57,990
Soldiers of the 87th Brigade...

402
00:18:58,830 --> 00:19:00,030
All rise!

403
00:19:01,470 --> 00:19:02,400
Salute!

404
00:19:02,910 --> 00:19:03,690
At ease!

405
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:10,120
All of you have fought bravely

406
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:11,250
and shed your blood.

407
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:12,830
Today, we repelled the enemy's attack

408
00:19:12,830 --> 00:19:14,150
11 times.

409
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:16,350
The position changed hands several times,

410
00:19:16,350 --> 00:19:18,080
but every time, we took it back!

411
00:19:18,340 --> 00:19:19,380
I, Yunkui,

412
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:21,750
thank you all.

413
00:19:22,350 --> 00:19:23,510
As I said before,

414
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,090
some of you

415
00:19:25,520 --> 00:19:26,520
are not soldiers,

416
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,060
but because the situation is desperate,

417
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:29,260
I couldn't let you go!

418
00:19:30,510 --> 00:19:32,700
The ground we stand on now

419
00:19:32,910 --> 00:19:34,170
is called Baijiazhai.

420
00:19:34,670 --> 00:19:35,870
The cotton grown here

421
00:19:36,390 --> 00:19:37,720
is exceptionally white

422
00:19:37,790 --> 00:19:39,720
and famous throughout the region.

423
00:19:39,910 --> 00:19:41,230
The cotton farmers here

424
00:19:41,230 --> 00:19:42,680
used to have a good life.

425
00:19:43,320 --> 00:19:45,190
But in just one morning,

426
00:19:46,070 --> 00:19:47,200
the Japanese devils

427
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:49,750
leveled this place to the ground

428
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,510
with their bombs!

429
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,620
Family after family

430
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:55,080
saw their hard-earned,

431
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,920
generational legacy—
built up over lifetimes—

432
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,200
destroyed by the enemy

433
00:19:58,270 --> 00:19:59,550
for no reason at all!

434
00:20:00,570 --> 00:20:01,430
The atrocities

435
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,640
the Japanese committed

436
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:03,750
in the northeast,

437
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,340
Peiping, and Tianjin—I need not elaborate.

438
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:08,000
But now,

439
00:20:08,270 --> 00:20:09,930
they want to occupy Shanghai,

440
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Shandong,

441
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,590
Shanxi,

442
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:14,160
and even all of China!

443
00:20:15,030 --> 00:20:16,070
By then...

444
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:19,230
how many families

445
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:22,390
will be destroyed like this?

446
00:20:23,060 --> 00:20:24,140
Today, right here,

447
00:20:24,170 --> 00:20:26,860
more than 500 of our soldiers
have died in battle.

448
00:20:26,860 --> 00:20:28,050
Why did they die?

449
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,250
Because they knew they couldn't retreat.

450
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,530
Why could they not retreat?

451
00:20:34,110 --> 00:20:36,240
Because the enemy
has reached our doorstep.

452
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,480
Wherever we retreat,

453
00:20:37,820 --> 00:20:40,210
the folks there will suffer!

454
00:20:41,030 --> 00:20:41,770
So,

455
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:43,970
we are not afraid to die!

456
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,590
We'll fight them

457
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,000
to the bitter end!

458
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:48,830
I, Yunkui,

459
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,270
sincerely ask every one of you to stay

460
00:20:51,270 --> 00:20:53,330
and fight the Japanese alongside us!

461
00:20:55,780 --> 00:20:56,860
Who wants to stay?

462
00:21:04,510 --> 00:21:05,480
I'll stay!

463
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:08,590
Those Japanese won't let us live,

464
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:09,720
so let's fight them!

465
00:21:09,790 --> 00:21:10,510
Yes!

466
00:21:10,630 --> 00:21:11,600
Let's fight them!

467
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:12,860
Yes, let's fight them!

468
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:13,590
Fight!

469
00:21:13,590 --> 00:21:14,720
Let's fight them!

470
00:21:15,030 --> 00:21:15,790
Good.

471
00:21:16,030 --> 00:21:17,200
Those who want to stay

472
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,510
are all brave men!

473
00:21:19,780 --> 00:21:20,740
I'm staying too.

474
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:24,710
Before, the Japanese burst into my home,

475
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:25,680
killed my dad,

476
00:21:26,190 --> 00:21:28,230
and even crapped in our cooking pot.

477
00:21:29,090 --> 00:21:29,850
They...

478
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:31,790
never treated

479
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:33,320
us Chinese as human beings.

480
00:21:33,430 --> 00:21:34,560
I'm staying

481
00:21:34,590 --> 00:21:35,790
to kill the Japanese.

482
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:39,430
Officer...

483
00:21:41,570 --> 00:21:42,490
What...

484
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:45,440
What about those who don't want to stay?

485
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,560
Those who don't want to stay

486
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:50,270
can leave.

487
00:21:55,390 --> 00:21:56,220
Blindy.

488
00:21:57,130 --> 00:21:58,320
Go back if you want.

489
00:21:59,060 --> 00:22:00,660
I've long had no home anyway.

490
00:22:00,770 --> 00:22:03,010
My dad was buried alive by the Japanese.

491
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:06,220
My mom was burned alive by the Japanese.

492
00:22:06,550 --> 00:22:09,340
My little sister was tied to a vat
and violated to death

493
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:10,660
by the Japanese.

494
00:22:11,220 --> 00:22:12,940
She wasn't even 14.

495
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:16,790
I've wanted to kill the Japanese
for a long time.

496
00:22:16,810 --> 00:22:17,640
Officer,

497
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,860
do those who stay get guns?

498
00:22:19,890 --> 00:22:20,610
Yes.

499
00:22:21,890 --> 00:22:22,850
I'll stay!

500
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:24,730
Even one kill makes it worth it!

501
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:27,500
The Japanese burn, kill, loot, and ravage.

502
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:29,230
After brutalizing our people,

503
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:31,850
too cheap to waste bullets,

504
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:34,090
they simply tie a person's legs

505
00:22:34,140 --> 00:22:35,110
to bamboo poles

506
00:22:35,430 --> 00:22:36,520
and let go—

507
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:38,800
ripping them apart alive.

508
00:22:39,260 --> 00:22:41,500
Calling them animals

509
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:43,820
would be an insult to animals!

510
00:22:44,350 --> 00:22:46,320
I'm going to fight them to the death.

511
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:47,050
To the death!

512
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:48,950
Yes, to the death!

513
00:22:49,550 --> 00:22:50,480
To the death!

514
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:53,400
To the death!

515
00:23:06,050 --> 00:23:06,880
Soldiers...

516
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:13,680
Where are you going?

517
00:23:15,680 --> 00:23:16,940
You worthless wretch.

518
00:23:17,350 --> 00:23:18,590
You dare to leave?

519
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:21,720
Why can't I leave?

520
00:23:21,750 --> 00:23:23,400
Why can't I leave?

521
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:24,660
The whole nation is fighting the Japanese.

522
00:23:24,660 --> 00:23:26,580
Aren't you part of the nation?

523
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,100
You just said it yourself—

524
00:23:28,230 --> 00:23:29,790
I'm a worthless wretch!

525
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:32,120
I'm too worthless to be part of it, okay?

526
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:36,070
If you say another word
to undermine morale,

527
00:23:36,070 --> 00:23:37,940
I'll shoot you right now!

528
00:23:38,110 --> 00:23:38,920
Shoot me then!

529
00:23:39,180 --> 00:23:40,250
Shoot me then!

530
00:23:40,660 --> 00:23:42,000
The commander just said it himself.

531
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,870
He said those who want to leave can leave,

532
00:23:43,870 --> 00:23:45,800
and those who want to stay can stay!

533
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:49,800
Come here.

534
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:51,030
Come with me and look!

535
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:51,920
Stop!

536
00:23:53,030 --> 00:23:54,030
Look who this is!

537
00:23:55,220 --> 00:23:55,980
Look!

538
00:23:56,570 --> 00:23:57,820
Look who this is!

539
00:23:58,480 --> 00:24:00,710
He just died right in front of you.

540
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:02,330
How did he die?

541
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:04,140
And what did he die for?

542
00:24:14,510 --> 00:24:17,030
He was killed by a stray bullet!

543
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:19,780
He didn't die saving me!

544
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:22,570
What does that have to do with me?

545
00:24:23,530 --> 00:24:24,930
I'll kowtow to him, okay?

546
00:24:25,270 --> 00:24:26,470
I'll kowtow to him!

547
00:24:27,110 --> 00:24:28,370
Company Commander Yu,

548
00:24:28,590 --> 00:24:29,960
you were a great hero!

549
00:24:29,980 --> 00:24:32,400
I kowtow to you!

550
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:35,870
Company Commander Yu,

551
00:24:35,870 --> 00:24:37,000
bullets don't have eyes.

552
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,030
You wouldn't blame me, right?

553
00:24:38,030 --> 00:24:40,690
I'll burn incense for you every year
from now on.

554
00:24:40,770 --> 00:24:42,370
I'm just an ordinary nobody.

555
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,840
You were a great hero.

556
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,000
You couldn't expect us

557
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,980
to die for you!

558
00:24:49,350 --> 00:24:49,880
Platoon Leader Wang,

559
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:50,790
I'll kowtow to you too.

560
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:51,310
I kowtow to you.

561
00:24:51,310 --> 00:24:52,620
Just let me go.

562
00:24:52,750 --> 00:24:53,440
Let me go.

563
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,550
I don't know how to use a gun,

564
00:24:54,550 --> 00:24:55,510
and I can't kill.

565
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:56,830
What's the point of keeping me here?

566
00:24:56,830 --> 00:24:58,680
Just so I can die?

567
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,630
What the hell are you kneeling for?

568
00:25:03,110 --> 00:25:04,240
Kong Erbao...

569
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:08,550
Why are your knees so weak?

570
00:25:09,590 --> 00:25:11,880
Are you even a man?

571
00:25:13,270 --> 00:25:15,130
Are you even human?

572
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:19,160
Get lost!

573
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,400
Stop right there!

574
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:18,100
Do you dare look at
Company Commander Yu's face?

575
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,510
Make him look at it!

576
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:24,640
Look!

577
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:28,680
Do you dare?

578
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:31,320
Look closely.

579
00:26:32,430 --> 00:26:33,510
You die for us,

580
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,470
but who do we die for?

581
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:37,580
Is China your country or not?

582
00:26:38,110 --> 00:26:39,200
Is it?

583
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,770
Just because of you,

584
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:43,070
back in the camp,

585
00:26:43,070 --> 00:26:45,330
I almost executed Company Commander Yu.

586
00:26:45,510 --> 00:26:46,910
What did he say to me then?

587
00:26:47,110 --> 00:26:48,700
"Tell my mom,

588
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,820
I died on the battlefield!"

589
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:53,120
All the soldiers here

590
00:26:53,310 --> 00:26:55,170
were pleading for me to spare him.

591
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:56,460
And what did he say?

592
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:58,960
"I want to die facing the enemy."

593
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,440
He kept his promise today.

594
00:27:02,270 --> 00:27:03,330
But what about you?

595
00:27:03,510 --> 00:27:05,270
What did you do?

596
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:07,610
Let me tell you,

597
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:09,410
anyone can leave today,

598
00:27:09,590 --> 00:27:10,640
but not you.

599
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:13,380
My righteous lord!

600
00:27:13,910 --> 00:27:15,490
I'm just a worm!

601
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:17,950
I was born a worm!

602
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:19,250
A worm's life may be worthless,

603
00:27:19,250 --> 00:27:21,000
but it's still a life!

604
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:23,640
I just live by my own rules!

605
00:27:23,670 --> 00:27:26,220
How am I getting in your way?

606
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,410
I'm telling you,

607
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:31,350
China has fallen to this state today

608
00:27:31,350 --> 00:27:32,550
because there are too many spineless worms

609
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:33,080
like you!

610
00:27:33,110 --> 00:27:34,660
Utterly hopeless! Beyond all help!

611
00:27:34,660 --> 00:27:35,590
Do you know that?

612
00:27:35,750 --> 00:27:36,680
I'm telling you,

613
00:27:36,790 --> 00:27:38,880
today I'm going to fix

614
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:40,640
that slug-like nature of yours.

615
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:41,640
Anyone can leave,

616
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,850
but not you!

617
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:44,550
You just said it there...

618
00:27:44,550 --> 00:27:48,160
-A gentleman's word is his bond!
-Who told you I'm a gentleman?

619
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,510
Who told you that?

620
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:51,470
I'm telling you,

621
00:27:51,550 --> 00:27:52,750
you're staying today

622
00:27:52,830 --> 00:27:54,240
and watching us die.

623
00:27:54,270 --> 00:27:55,270
Watching me die!

624
00:27:55,310 --> 00:27:56,440
But I'm telling you,

625
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,440
I'll likely be the last one to die.

626
00:27:58,440 --> 00:27:59,270
From now on,

627
00:27:59,270 --> 00:28:00,270
you're my orderly.

628
00:28:00,270 --> 00:28:02,730
You're not to leave my side
for a single step!

629
00:28:08,350 --> 00:28:09,480
Tell his mom

630
00:28:09,980 --> 00:28:11,510
he died on the battlefield,

631
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:13,880
facing the Japanese!

632
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,350
Yes, sir!

633
00:28:23,750 --> 00:28:24,590
Move.

634
00:28:25,750 --> 00:28:26,510
Move!

635
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:27,960
Move!

636
00:28:28,070 --> 00:28:29,110
Move!

637
00:28:29,790 --> 00:28:33,360
[Nanjing]

638
00:28:35,830 --> 00:28:36,650
Father,

639
00:28:37,310 --> 00:28:38,570
I've put your tea here.

640
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:41,270
Rest early.

641
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:44,000
That's all.

642
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:45,960
You go rest early too.

643
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:47,390
Sweet dreams.

644
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:48,720
Sweet dreams.

645
00:29:00,790 --> 00:29:08,980
♪ There are nine moons in the sky ♪

646
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:17,890
♪ Nine moons reflected on the water ♪

647
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:26,270
♪ Nine moons shining over the land ♪

648
00:29:27,660 --> 00:29:36,040
♪ Nine moons hidden among the clouds ♪

649
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:34,240
Normally,

650
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:36,590
a task this important
wouldn't fall to someone at your level.

651
00:29:36,590 --> 00:29:38,050
But in times of emergency,

652
00:29:38,310 --> 00:29:40,440
we have to make the best of what we have.

653
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:47,350
This mark means
there is hope for treatment.

654
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:54,910
This means there is no hope.

655
00:29:55,640 --> 00:29:57,920
But we can't tell the soldiers the truth.

656
00:30:01,580 --> 00:30:03,040
Soldiers who get this mark

657
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:04,610
can only wait to die.

658
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,190
Those with severe injuries

659
00:30:06,190 --> 00:30:08,090
and a weak will to live

660
00:30:08,630 --> 00:30:10,480
will very likely die

661
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:13,410
during treatment or even afterward.

662
00:30:13,870 --> 00:30:16,980
That would be a waste
of supplies and manpower.

663
00:30:18,110 --> 00:30:19,770
A failed rescue

664
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:21,880
wastes time that could be

665
00:30:22,160 --> 00:30:24,760
spent on soldiers
who might actually survive.

666
00:30:25,270 --> 00:30:27,330
When I first took over this position,

667
00:30:27,630 --> 00:30:31,440
[Dispensary]

668
00:30:28,270 --> 00:30:29,730
I wanted to save everyone,

669
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:32,150
marking as many with circles as I could.

670
00:30:32,150 --> 00:30:33,160
Later,

671
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:35,300
the director scolded me harshly.

672
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:36,790
He said...

673
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:39,160
I wasn't saving people

674
00:30:40,030 --> 00:30:42,200
but actually harming them.

675
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,330
This is wartime.

676
00:30:44,620 --> 00:30:46,020
We're military doctors.

677
00:30:46,070 --> 00:30:47,370
We must stay rational.

678
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:48,750
We must know when to make hard choices.

679
00:30:48,750 --> 00:30:50,550
Only then can we save more lives.

680
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:52,760
I understand the reasoning,

681
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:53,400
but I...

682
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:56,330
You're the one
deciding whether they live or die now.

683
00:30:57,830 --> 00:30:58,590
It's cruel,

684
00:30:58,590 --> 00:30:59,720
but this is reality.

685
00:31:08,660 --> 00:31:11,660
[Dispensary]

686
00:31:16,660 --> 00:31:21,640
[Dispensary]

687
00:31:29,750 --> 00:31:30,950
Division Commander,

688
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,310
Luodian is flat with no mountains,

689
00:31:32,310 --> 00:31:33,400
and the groundwater is shallow.

690
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,440
We simply have no way

691
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:35,770
to dig proper trenches.

692
00:31:35,790 --> 00:31:37,270
We can only build
some basic fortifications.

693
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:38,240
But these fortifications

694
00:31:38,240 --> 00:31:39,400
are practically useless

695
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:40,110
against

696
00:31:40,110 --> 00:31:41,440
the enemy's heavy artillery.

697
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:42,920
We can only hold the line
with our flesh and blood.

698
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:44,160
But fighting the Japanese like this

699
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,720
puts us at a tremendous disadvantage!

700
00:31:45,720 --> 00:31:46,750
My suggestion is

701
00:31:47,110 --> 00:31:48,720
to take advantage of the enemy's inability
to detect us at night,

702
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,270
use our geographical advantage,

703
00:31:50,270 --> 00:31:51,590
and concentrate our firepower
to catch them off guard,

704
00:31:51,590 --> 00:31:52,510
launching a surprise attack.

705
00:31:52,510 --> 00:31:55,430
Right now, the priority is
to hold your position.

706
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:57,280
Hold the lines one by one

707
00:31:57,350 --> 00:31:58,600
to buy time.

708
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,590
An offensive defense

709
00:31:59,590 --> 00:32:01,300
can also buy us time!

710
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,510
If we defeat the enemy,

711
00:32:02,510 --> 00:32:03,880
we gain time when they retreat.

712
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:05,030
Even if we can't push them back,

713
00:32:05,030 --> 00:32:06,200
we'll disrupt their rhythm.

714
00:32:06,200 --> 00:32:07,390
Their rate of advance will be slowed,

715
00:32:07,390 --> 00:32:08,750
which also buys us time!

716
00:32:08,830 --> 00:32:12,110
On the battlefield,
the key is to act as one.

717
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,310
Without orders, you must not act rashly—

718
00:32:14,310 --> 00:32:16,440
or you will face a court-martial!

719
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:19,720
Rest assured,

720
00:32:20,160 --> 00:32:21,670
I'll consider your plan.

721
00:32:22,070 --> 00:32:22,590
In a few days...

722
00:32:22,590 --> 00:32:23,750
Division Commander!

723
00:32:23,750 --> 00:32:25,160
I fear the opportunity
will slip away in an instant.

724
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:26,070
In a few more days,

725
00:32:26,070 --> 00:32:27,000
once the dozen or so Japanese detachments

726
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:28,030
are fully deployed,

727
00:32:28,030 --> 00:32:29,880
we will truly have no chance left!

728
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:31,140
Carry out your orders!

729
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,130
Defending like this

730
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:38,030
will only increase casualties.

731
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:39,400
I believe the Division Commander's concern

732
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:40,260
is that he fears

733
00:32:40,270 --> 00:32:42,310
we'll fight like the Hongkou assault—

734
00:32:42,310 --> 00:32:43,260
with enormous casualties.

735
00:32:43,170 --> 00:32:43,740
[87th Brigade,
National Revolutionary Army]

736
00:32:43,310 --> 00:32:44,590
I think he's just afraid of
taking responsibility!

737
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:44,350
[Feng Duoyi,
Commander of the 805th Regiment]

738
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:45,240
Sir.

739
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:46,920
How is this different
from a suicide mission?

740
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,070
Sir, I need to go to the latrine!

741
00:32:48,070 --> 00:32:48,960
Hold it!

742
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:53,620
Go ahead.

743
00:33:05,870 --> 00:33:06,950
This is Sun Huaiyi.

744
00:33:08,910 --> 00:33:11,100
[Lu Yun, Chief of Staff, 187th Division,
National Revolutionary Army]

745
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:11,480
Generalissimo, this is Sun Huaiyi.

746
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:13,520
Please give your instructions.

747
00:33:13,770 --> 00:33:16,170
[Liao Fengnian, 187th Division
Deputy Commander, NRA]

748
00:33:14,030 --> 00:33:14,720
Yes!

749
00:33:15,190 --> 00:33:16,410
Morale is very high!

750
00:33:16,750 --> 00:33:18,640
This subordinate guarantees
we will accomplish the mission

751
00:33:18,640 --> 00:33:20,200
and hold Baijiazhai!

752
00:33:35,130 --> 00:33:37,390
What do you think of Zhang Yunkui's idea?

753
00:33:40,880 --> 00:33:41,790
Division Commander,

754
00:33:41,790 --> 00:33:44,050
I think Zhang Yunkui makes a valid point.

755
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:44,920
Look,

756
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:45,830
without heavy weapon cover,

757
00:33:45,830 --> 00:33:47,290
we are completely exposed

758
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:48,830
to the enemy's

759
00:33:48,830 --> 00:33:51,070
aerial bombs and heavy artillery fire.

760
00:33:51,350 --> 00:33:52,480
And the terrain

761
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:53,270
is not suitable

762
00:33:53,270 --> 00:33:55,000
for building defense in depth.

763
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:57,190
So every unit is basically
fighting on its own.

764
00:33:57,190 --> 00:33:58,250
If this continues,

765
00:33:58,510 --> 00:34:00,920
our troops will eventually
be worn down completely.

766
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:02,720
It is only a matter of time before

767
00:34:03,830 --> 00:34:05,480
the Japanese break through
our defensive line.

768
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:06,480
Division Commander.

769
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:08,510
I also think
Zhang Yunkui's suggestion is feasible.

770
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:09,880
If we strike proactively from the flank

771
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:10,880
and hit them hard,

772
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,880
we might disrupt their deployment.

773
00:34:16,030 --> 00:34:17,960
This is such a large-scale battle.

774
00:34:18,190 --> 00:34:21,120
All the elite forces of our army
have been committed.

775
00:34:21,460 --> 00:34:24,550
Even the slightest deviation could
throw the whole plan into chaos.

776
00:34:24,550 --> 00:34:26,630
Never mind a mere brigade commander
like him—

777
00:34:26,630 --> 00:34:28,360
even I, as division commander,

778
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:30,090
or the army commander above me,

779
00:34:30,110 --> 00:34:31,760
or the army group commander—

780
00:34:32,190 --> 00:34:33,989
who can actually call the shots?

781
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:36,840
The Generalissimo
personally oversees everything.

782
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:37,960
The theater commanders

783
00:34:37,960 --> 00:34:39,560
have become his messengers.

784
00:34:43,510 --> 00:34:46,670
What's emphasized now is
that the whole army acts as one—

785
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:48,940
everyone follows orders.

786
00:34:52,489 --> 00:34:54,670
Private First Class Liu Zhenbao,

787
00:34:54,670 --> 00:34:56,469
211th Regiment, 36th Division!

788
00:35:05,100 --> 00:35:06,060
Which unit are you from?

789
00:35:06,060 --> 00:35:07,740
Sergeant Wu Wenjie, Squad Leader,

790
00:35:07,740 --> 00:35:09,540
216th Regiment, 36th Division!

791
00:35:11,550 --> 00:35:13,250
How did he end up with burns this severe?

792
00:35:13,250 --> 00:35:14,000
The enemy shells

793
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,550
were about to land on our position.

794
00:35:15,550 --> 00:35:17,430
He tried to seize the light machine gun
at the position.

795
00:35:17,430 --> 00:35:19,100
But the gun was too hot!

796
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:20,510
He grabbed it and ran with it in his arms!

797
00:35:20,510 --> 00:35:22,770
If it weren't for that light machine gun,

798
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:24,250
the position would have fallen long ago.

799
00:35:24,250 --> 00:35:26,710
Doctor, can our squad leader
still be saved?

800
00:35:32,220 --> 00:35:34,490
[Casualty Tag]

801
00:35:39,420 --> 00:35:45,990
[Casualty Tag]

802
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:50,420
Give this to the nurse over there.

803
00:35:50,420 --> 00:35:52,020
Thank you, doctor! Let's go!

804
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:06,430
Let's begin.

805
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:10,890
Corporal of the 528th Regiment,
88th Division.

806
00:36:11,710 --> 00:36:15,630
Corporal of the 528th Regiment,
88th Division.

807
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:16,880
Ma Jisheng.

808
00:36:18,030 --> 00:36:19,070
Ma Jisheng.

809
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:22,960
Corporal of the 583rd Regiment,
98th Division.

810
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:26,760
Corporal of the 583rd Regiment,
98th Division.

811
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:33,070
Name unknown.

812
00:36:35,670 --> 00:36:39,440
Corporal of the 583rd Regiment,
98th Division,

813
00:36:39,590 --> 00:36:40,630
name unknown.

814
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:47,300
[Soldier's Identity Information]

815
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:42,760
67th Division...

816
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:44,100
The moon shines bright

817
00:36:44,510 --> 00:36:47,470
as gunsmoke blankets both banks
of the Yangtze River.

818
00:36:47,470 --> 00:36:50,320
Blood stains the earth beneath our feet.

819
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:53,440
The enemy's strength already
far outweighs ours.

820
00:36:53,440 --> 00:36:57,290
Meanwhile, the KMT's command system
is corrupt and chaotic—

821
00:36:57,500 --> 00:36:59,120
commanders bypass the chain of command
during battle,

822
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:00,930
then shift blame
and evade responsibility afterward.

823
00:37:00,930 --> 00:37:03,970
Bravery is treated as expendable manpower.

824
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,590
All that bloodshed

825
00:37:06,610 --> 00:37:09,690
can never cleanse
the deep-rooted corruption.

826
00:37:10,210 --> 00:37:13,330
The spiritual mire of old China

827
00:37:13,350 --> 00:37:17,620
awaits a thorough cleansing.

828
00:37:22,550 --> 00:37:24,230
Workers, peasants, soldiers, students,
and merchants—

829
00:37:24,230 --> 00:37:26,030
let us all rise together
to save the nation.

830
00:37:26,030 --> 00:37:29,690
Pick up our hammers, swords, and guns,

831
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:33,190
and walk out of the factories,
fields, and classrooms.

832
00:37:30,520 --> 00:37:33,360
[Frontline Entertainment Troupe]

833
00:37:33,190 --> 00:37:34,480
Let's go to the front line.

834
00:37:33,610 --> 00:37:38,580
[Frontline Entertainment Troupe]

835
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:38,760
Let's go to the battlefield
for national liberation!

836
00:37:39,190 --> 00:37:40,910
Step by step,

837
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,770
side by side,

838
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:46,540
our ranks grow ever stronger!

839
00:37:46,590 --> 00:37:50,190
The struggle of oppressed people
all over the world

840
00:37:50,190 --> 00:37:54,240
moves in the same direction!

841
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:57,920
Millions raise their voices in resistance!

842
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,830
Millions sing

843
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:03,690
songs of revolutionary struggle!

844
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:07,510
We will build a people's national defense!

845
00:38:07,510 --> 00:38:09,480
Everyone, rise and arm yourselves!

846
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:11,280
Down with traitors and lackeys,

847
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:13,030
and point your guns outward!

848
00:38:13,190 --> 00:38:14,280
We must recover lost land

849
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:16,960
and overthrow Japanese imperialism.

850
00:38:17,030 --> 00:38:20,880
Kill all the robbers of the old world.

851
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,340
Bravo!

852
00:38:22,770 --> 00:38:29,300
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

853
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:29,400
The sorghum leaves are so green.

854
00:38:30,030 --> 00:38:35,230
On September 18th,
the Japanese soldiers came.

855
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:40,300
First, they occupied the powder magazine,

856
00:38:40,080 --> 00:38:43,610
[Yu Shuzhen]

857
00:38:40,710 --> 00:38:43,030
then they occupied...

858
00:38:45,230 --> 00:38:45,960
Sing!

859
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:47,100
Keep singing!

860
00:38:47,230 --> 00:38:48,280
Continue the opera!

861
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,400
Gentlemen and lords,

862
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:50,510
don't rush.

863
00:38:50,710 --> 00:38:52,310
I'll ask her what's going on.

864
00:38:52,950 --> 00:38:54,400
I say, Miss Xiang,

865
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:57,140
why did you stop halfway through the song

866
00:38:57,320 --> 00:38:58,960
as if you'd run out of breath?

867
00:38:59,030 --> 00:39:00,190
Nonsense.

868
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:03,030
Could I still be sitting here
if I'd run out of breath?

869
00:39:03,030 --> 00:39:05,190
I just can't muster up the energy.

870
00:39:07,510 --> 00:39:08,920
Miss Xiang says

871
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:11,650
she just can't find the spirit for it.

872
00:39:11,860 --> 00:39:12,880
Why can't she muster up the energy?

873
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,110
What kind of talk is that?

874
00:39:14,110 --> 00:39:16,510
She's afraid you officers and soldiers
won't tip her.

875
00:39:16,510 --> 00:39:17,400
Impossible!

876
00:39:17,630 --> 00:39:18,150
Quick,

877
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,400
show off a unique skill

878
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,600
to please the lords!

879
00:39:22,630 --> 00:39:23,440
Come on!

880
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:24,930
Come on!

881
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:26,190
Bravo! Come on!

882
00:39:25,820 --> 00:39:32,150
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

883
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:37,580
Bravo! Bravo!

884
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:40,880
Bravo! Bravo!

885
00:39:44,590 --> 00:39:45,800
-Why did she fall?
-Help her up!

886
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,070
What's going on?

887
00:39:48,110 --> 00:39:48,920
Get up.

888
00:39:50,030 --> 00:39:50,960
Get up!

889
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:54,650
You are asking for a beating, aren't you?

890
00:39:56,920 --> 00:39:58,440
Stop hitting her! Stop hitting her!

891
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:00,590
Stop hitting her! Stop hitting her!

892
00:40:01,260 --> 00:40:03,740
[Anti-Enemy Performance Troupe]

893
00:40:01,630 --> 00:40:02,920
So you can't muster any energy, huh?

894
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:03,920
Stop hitting me!

895
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:06,470
I'll kill you! I'll kill you!

896
00:40:06,880 --> 00:40:07,480
Don't run!

897
00:40:07,510 --> 00:40:08,450
I was wrong!

898
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:10,800
Stop hitting me!

899
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:11,580
Stop!

900
00:40:15,230 --> 00:40:16,170
What are you doing?

901
00:40:16,170 --> 00:40:17,040
Stay out of it!

902
00:40:18,110 --> 00:40:19,820
How can you hit her?

903
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:20,890
She's my girl!

904
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,720
I can do whatever I want with her!

905
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:23,880
We're all poor people here!

906
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,110
No one is allowed to bully anyone!

907
00:40:25,110 --> 00:40:25,710
Exactly!

908
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:26,710
Hitting someone is not okay!

909
00:40:26,710 --> 00:40:27,560
That's right!

910
00:40:27,590 --> 00:40:29,000
Sir, it's part of the show!

911
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:29,630
-Cut the crap.
-Show?

912
00:40:29,630 --> 00:40:31,590
You can't hit a girl even
if you're acting, right?

913
00:40:31,590 --> 00:40:32,830
Come on, hit him!

914
00:40:33,320 --> 00:40:34,230
Hit him!

915
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:35,890
Hit him! Hit him!

916
00:40:35,910 --> 00:40:37,370
Stop hitting him! Stop it!

917
00:40:37,710 --> 00:40:38,800
They were just acting!

918
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:40,230
-Yes, sir.
-Can't you see?

919
00:40:40,230 --> 00:40:40,860
We were acting.

920
00:40:40,860 --> 00:40:41,840
You were acting.

921
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:42,550
He was only faking!

922
00:40:42,550 --> 00:40:44,000
You can't really hit her,
even if you're acting.

923
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:44,810
It was acting.

924
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:45,520
Fake hits.

925
00:40:45,630 --> 00:40:46,590
It's fine! They were just acting!

926
00:40:46,590 --> 00:40:48,650
-Let's go.
-He didn't really hit her.

927
00:40:48,810 --> 00:40:49,950
It was fake. Fake!

928
00:40:49,980 --> 00:40:51,190
Sit down. Everyone, sit down.

929
00:40:51,190 --> 00:40:51,590
Fake.

930
00:40:51,670 --> 00:40:52,190
Alright.

931
00:40:52,190 --> 00:40:53,120
Let's continue.

932
00:40:53,410 --> 00:40:54,950
You bad old man!

933
00:40:55,710 --> 00:40:56,520
Don't run!

934
00:40:56,550 --> 00:40:57,280
Xiaoyue!

935
00:40:58,110 --> 00:40:59,640
Can you help me comb my hair?

936
00:40:59,670 --> 00:41:00,440
Okay.

937
00:41:07,110 --> 00:41:08,240
Let me see this side.

938
00:41:18,110 --> 00:41:19,510
Han Xiaoyue!

939
00:41:33,260 --> 00:41:35,190
You're not helping me comb my hair?

940
00:41:35,810 --> 00:41:37,390
Xiaoyue, Xiaoyue...

941
00:41:37,580 --> 00:41:38,330
Xiaoyue.

942
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:40,040
You're alive.

943
00:41:40,150 --> 00:41:41,340
I'm alive. I'm alive.

944
00:41:41,340 --> 00:41:42,890
I'm alive. I'm alive.

945
00:41:42,920 --> 00:41:46,570
Do you know
I've been looking for you like crazy?

946
00:41:46,770 --> 00:41:49,090
I know. I know.

947
00:41:53,330 --> 00:41:55,000
I'm alive. I'm alive.

948
00:41:58,850 --> 00:42:00,210
Are you hurt?

949
00:42:01,330 --> 00:42:02,200
I'm fine.

950
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,290
Why are you wearing a military uniform?

951
00:42:05,290 --> 00:42:06,330
Kong Erbao!

952
00:42:07,020 --> 00:42:08,930
I was dragged here as a conscript.

953
00:42:09,110 --> 00:42:10,960
How come they drafted you?

954
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:12,230
Let's go find your superior.

955
00:42:12,230 --> 00:42:14,000
Can you get out of this?

956
00:42:14,550 --> 00:42:15,500
I'm telling you,

957
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:17,180
these soldiers are all thugs.

958
00:42:17,550 --> 00:42:19,000
The last time I tried to escape,

959
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:20,190
I almost got executed by them.

960
00:42:20,190 --> 00:42:21,250
What are you doing?

961
00:42:24,880 --> 00:42:26,080
Platoon Leader Wang.

962
00:42:26,940 --> 00:42:29,450
This... This is my fiancée.

963
00:42:30,470 --> 00:42:31,840
She's with the troop-cheering squad.

964
00:42:31,840 --> 00:42:32,940
We ran into each other here.

965
00:42:32,940 --> 00:42:33,690
I...

966
00:42:34,290 --> 00:42:36,290
I just wanted to talk to her for a bit.

967
00:42:37,080 --> 00:42:38,000
Your fiancée?

968
00:42:47,580 --> 00:42:48,420
Go ahead.

969
00:42:52,150 --> 00:42:52,880
We...

970
00:42:53,670 --> 00:42:54,930
We'd like to talk here.

971
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:03,030
Then talk now.
